title: Can I restore the "Regulator Labels" section under "About phone" without factory reset?
content:
After upgrading and setting up Google Fi, the "About phone > Regulatory labels" information has disappeared. When I first got the phone, that section showed I had a G020E and would require a physical SIM. But now that section just looks like this:

Where's the info?! I'd just like to be able to prove that the phone is a G020E and not a G020G. Thanks!
